  "local_port": 36924,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I import contacts from basic mobile to smartphone?",
  "response": "Importing contacts from a basic mobile phone (feature phone) to a smartphone can be done in several ways. Here are the most common methods:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Using a SIM Card**\n   - **On the Basic Phone:**\n     1. Go to the **Contacts** app.\n     2. Select the option to **Copy Contacts to SIM Card** (this varies by phone model).\n     3. Choose the contacts you want to copy or select **All Contacts**.\n   - **On the Smartphone:**\n     1. Insert the SIM card into the smartphone.\n     2. Open the **Contacts** app.\n     3. Go to **Settings** or **Manage Contacts** and select **Import from SIM Card**.\n     4. Choose where to save the contacts (e.g., phone memory or Google account).\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Using Bluetooth**\n   - **On the Basic Phone:**\n     1. Go to the **Contacts** app.\n     2. Select the contacts you want to transfer.\n     3. Choose the option to **Send via Bluetooth**.\n   - **On the Smartphone:**\n     1. Enable Bluetooth on both devices.\n     2. Pair the two devices (you may need to enter a PIN).\n     3. Accept the incoming transfer on the smartphone.\n     4. Save the transferred contacts to your smartphone.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Using a Computer**\n   - **Step 1: Export Contacts from Basic Phone**\n     1. Connect the basic phone to your computer using a USB cable.\n     2. Use the phone's software (if available) or file explorer to locate and export the contacts as a `.vcf` (vCard) file.\n   - **Step 2: Import Contacts to Smartphone**\n     1. Move the `.vcf` file to your smartphone (via email, cloud storage, or USB transfer).\n     2. Open the **Contacts** app on the smartphone and import the `.vcf` file.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Using Google Account**\n   - **Step 1: Export Contacts from Basic Phone**\n     1. Export contacts from the basic phone to a `.vcf` file (as described above).\n   - **Step 2: Import to Google Contacts**\n     1. Log in to your Google account on a computer.\n     2. Go to [Google Contacts](https://contacts.google.com).\n     3. Click **Import** and upload the `.vcf` file.\n   - **Step 3: Sync with Smartphone**\n     1. On your smartphone, go to **Settings > Accounts > Google**.\n     2. Ensure **Contacts Sync** is enabled.\n     3. Open the **Contacts** app, and your imported contacts will appear.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Using Third-Party Apps**\n   - Some basic phones support apps like **SHAREit** or **Xender** for transferring contacts.\n   - Install the app on both devices and follow the on-screen instructions to transfer contacts.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Using a Cloud Service**\n   - Export contacts from the basic phone to a `.vcf` file and upload it to a cloud service like Google Drive, Dropbox, or OneDrive.\n   - Access the file on your smartphone and import it into the Contacts app.\n\n---\n\nIf your basic phone has limited functionality, the **SIM card** or **Bluetooth** methods are often the easiest. For future-proofing, saving contacts to a **Google account** is highly recommended.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
